In chat
иииииии
  Whilst chatting there are various things you can do apart from chatting to the user. You can spool the input or output, quit the user (in two ways, explained below) and you can spool files to the user. (Soon you'll be able to ZModem transfer too, hopefully!)...
  There are two types of quitting from the chat that the sysop can do. He can press `Quit User` which does the same as the user pressing Ctrl C or Ctrl D, and he can do `Back to BBS` which forces the user back to the BBS. They both have their adantages and disadvantages. Generally, use Back to BBS when the user is finding it difficult to quit. It is the easiest way out, as it sends the user straight back to the BBS.
  Dragging a file to the chat window will spool it as if the sysop was typing it in. It isn't the best way to send text (The best way is by file through the file areas, but it is OK if it is short, and contains something useful in, which you want to demonstrate to the user.
  In the next version I hope to have incorporated a rudimentary file transfer facility that will allow the sysop to send files to the user and vice-versa. This will be the ZModem protocol.

Logfile
иииииии
  I have included a way of logging what is happening to Natter. This simply logs things such as users entering the door, the sysop attempting to force a user into a door and such like. This should not be mixed up with the `ErrorLog` file, which when present, will make the icon slightly different.

