Development

-- Decided to start a `previous-versions` list. Richard Murray will enjoy  --
--         reading some `new` features to add to his chat appie ;-)        --
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version 1.41

Run !Natter with parameter `-c` it will go into `config` mode (same as pressing ALT and d/clicking).. Good for folks like John Stonier who have the memory to waste by leaving the application loaded so they can quickly configure it. ;-)

Version 1.43
_ _ _ _
Forcing a chat with !Natter when in config mode will no longer quit after the chat has been done, so force chats can be started by the configure-mode `chat` application. Neat eh?

_ _ _ _
If a user drops carrier whilst paging the sysop, the application will quit.

_ _ _ _
If for some reason the pager has been loaded for longer than 15 minutes (15*60*100 = 90 000 centisecs) (If the server is ever caught out by a user dropping carrier), it will automatically quit. It will _NOT_ set the status byte to 0, as in this time there could've been another user logon, and he might just be in a door ;-)
_ _ _ _

ArmBBS sysops, note that when you return users after a `force`d connection, please remember to redisplay the menu (by pressing `?`).. as if you don't it just leave's the user with a blank screen..
